ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete

Valid options are:

create

(default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked

delete

Remove one group pools from this session

clear_all

Removes all group pools from this session.

modify

Modifies group pools from this session.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete options are not supported for IxTclProtocol. Valid choices are: create - (default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. delete - Remove one group pools from this session clear_all - Removes all group pools from this session. modify - Modifies group pools from this session. enable - Enables the given item provided by -handle. disable - Disables the given item provided by -handle.

Valid options are:

create

An existing multicast group/source pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. It is also used to add join/prune, sources and crpRanges to a Pim session.

delete

Remove one group pools from this session. Also used to remove join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.

modify

Modifies group pools from this session. Also used to modify join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.

clear_all

Removes all group pools from this session. Also removes all join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from the Pim session.

disable

Disable the given item provided by -handle

enable

Enable the given item provided by -handle

DEFAULT

create

-source_pool_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Associate source pool(s) with the group. The source pool(s) must be added beforehand through procedure emulation_multicast_source_config. Specify one or more source pool handle(s) for (S,G) entries. None for (*,G) entries. If one or more are specified, source-specific join/prune will be enabled; otherwise it is disabled. This parameter may be a list. If the case,all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Associate source pool(s) with the group. The source pool(s) must be added beforehand through procedure emulation_multicast_source_config. Specify one or more source pool handle(s) for (S,G) entries. None for (*,G) entries. If one or more are specified, source-specific join/prune will be enabled; otherwise it is disabled. This parameter may be a list. If the case, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length.

DEFAULT

 None

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Group membership handle that associates a group pool with a PIM session. This option is returned from previous call to this proc with "create" mode. In "modify" mode, membership handle must be used in conjunction with the session handle to identify the member group pool. If this is a list, all other parameters that can be listsshould have the same list length. As such, multiple router interfaceswill be created with the given parameters.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Group membership handle that associates a group pool with a PIM session. This option is returned from previous call to this proc with "create" mode. In "modify" mode, membership handle must be used in conjunction with the session handle to identify the member group pool. If this is a list, all other parameters that can be lists should have the same list length. As such, multiple router interfaces will be created with the given parameters.

DEFAULT

 None

-return_detailed_handles

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This argument determines if individual interface, session or router handles are returned by the current command. This applies only to the command on which it is specified. Setting this to 0 means that only NGPF-specific protocol stack handles will be returned. This will significantly decrease the size of command results and speed up script execution. The default is 0, meaning only protocol stack handles will be returned.

DEFAULT

0

Supported platforms Details

Specifies whether the membership pool is used to send or receive PIM messages. Note: no configuration required for receive mode.

Valid options are:

send

Sends Join/Prunes (downstream DR) messages.

register

Sends Register and NULL Register messages. (source DR)

candidate_rp

Creates new Candidate Rendez-Vous.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

Specifies whether the membership pool is used to send or receive PIM messages. Note: no configuration required for receive mode. Valid choices are: send - Sends Join/Prunes (downstream DR) messages. register - Sends Register and NULL Register messages. (source DR) and receive Stop-Register messages. candidate_rp - Creates new Candidate Rendez-Vous.

Valid options are:

send

Sends Join/Prunes (downstream DR) messages.

register

-pri_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

priorityType This indicates the type of priority to be held by the candidate RPs (CRPs). One of:same - (default) CRPs send advertisement messages with time invariant fixed priority as specified in CRP Advertisement Message Priority.incremental - Priority starts from the configured value and with every Priority Change Interval, the CRP's priority get incremented by 1.random - The start value is selected based on a pseudorandom number generator with every Priority Change Interval, when sending the next batch of CRP-Adv messages.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

priorityType This indicates the type of priority to be held by the candidate RPs (CRPs). One of: same - (default) CRPs send advertisement messages with time invariant fixed priority as specified in CRP Advertisement Message Priority. incremental - Priority starts from the configured value and with every Priority Change Interval, the CRPs priority get incremented by 1. random - The start value is selected based on a pseudorandom number generator with every Priority Change Interval, when sending the next batch of CRP-Adv messages.

Valid options are:

same

incremental

random

DEFAULT

 None

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete

Valid options are:

create

(default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked

delete

Remove one group pools from this session

clear_all

Removes all group pools from this session.

modify

Modifies group pools from this session.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete options are not supported for IxTclProtocol. Valid choices are: create - (default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. delete - Remove one group pools from this session clear_all - Removes all group pools from this session. modify - Modifies group pools from this session. enable - Enables the given item provided by -handle. disable - Disables the given item provided by -handle.

Valid options are:

create

An existing multicast group/source pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. It is also used to add join/prune, sources and crpRanges to a Pim session.

delete

Remove one group pools from this session. Also used to remove join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.

modify

Modifies group pools from this session. Also used to modify join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.

clear_all

Removes all group pools from this session. Also removes all join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from the Pim session.

disable

Disable the given item provided by -handle

enable

Enable the given item provided by -handle

DEFAULT

create

mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete

Valid options are:

create

(default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked

delete

Remove one group pools from this session

clear_all

Removes all group pools from this session.

modify

Modifies group pools from this session.

DEFAULT

 None

IxNetwork-NGPF

DESCRIPTION

This option defines the action to be taken. Note: modify and delete options are not supported for IxTclProtocol. Valid choices are: create - (default) An existing multicast group pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. delete - Remove one group pools from this session clear_all - Removes all group pools from this session. modify - Modifies group pools from this session. enable - Enables the given item provided by -handle. disable - Disables the given item provided by -handle.

Valid options are:

create

An existing multicast group/source pool is associated/linked with the specified PIM session. It is also used to add join/prune, sources and crpRanges to a Pim session.

delete

Remove one group pools from this session. Also used to remove join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.

modify

Modifies group pools from this session. Also used to modify join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from Pim session.

clear_all

Removes all group pools from this session. Also removes all join/prunes, sources and crpRanges from the Pim session.

disable

Disable the given item provided by -handle

enable

Enable the given item provided by -handle

DEFAULT

create
